    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Workflow 3 — Instagram Poster\n\nRuns on schedule (default: daily at 12:00). Picks the oldest `approved` row whose `scheduled_for` is empty or due, posts it as an Instagram carousel via Meta Graph API, and marks the row `posted`.\n\n### Setup (one-time)\n1. **Instagram Business or Creator account** linked to a Facebook Page.\n2. **Meta App** with `instagram_basic`, `instagram_content_publish`, `pages_show_list`, `pages_read_engagement` permissions, reviewed and approved.\n3. Generate a **long-lived Page access token** (~60 days) — refresh before expiry or set a reminder.\n4. Get the **Instagram Business Account ID** (not the @username) and paste it into `IG_USER_ID`.\n5. In n8n, create a **\"Query Auth\" credential** with `Name=access_token`, `Value=<your long-lived token>`. Attach it to all three Instagram HTTP nodes.\n\n### Post flow (per Meta Graph API)\n1. For each slide URL: POST `/media` with `image_url` + `is_carousel_item=true` → returns an item container ID.\n2. POST `/media` with `media_type=CAROUSEL` + `children=<csv of item IDs>` + `caption` → returns the carousel container ID.\n3. **Wait 30s** for Instagram to finish processing the container (skipping this often returns errors on publish).\n4. POST `/media_publish` with `creation_id=<carousel container ID>` → returns the live post ID.\n5. Update the sheet row: `status=posted`, `posted_at`, `instagram_post_id`.\n\n### Notes\n- The poster uses the **Bannerbear-hosted URLs** from `slide_urls` (Instagram fetches them server-side; they must be publicly accessible — Bannerbear's CDN is).\n- If you need to order posts by date, fill in the `scheduled_for` column (YYYY-MM-DD). Empty = post whenever it's the oldest approved.\n- Default schedule = 1 post/day at noon. Adjust the Schedule Trigger if you want a different cadence.\n- Failed posts: the row stays `approved`, so it retries on the next run. Check n8n execution logs for the actual API error.",
        "height": 580,
        "width": 600,
        "color": 4
      },
